Subject: follicle stimulating hormone [IMR:0100099]
Value: A major gonadotropin secreted by the adenohypophysis ( PITUITARY GLAND, ANTERIOR). Follicle-stimulating hormone stimulates GAMETOGENESIS and the supporting cells such as the ovarian GRANULOSA CELLS, the testicular SERTOLI CELLS, and LEYDIG CELLS. FSH consists of two noncovalently linked subunits, alpha and beta. Within a species, the alpha subunit is common in the three pituitary glycoprotein hormones (TSH, LH, and FSH), but the beta subunit is unique and confers its biological specificity.

Subject: nucleotide [IMR:0001349]
Value: A nucleotide consists of a nitrogen-containing base, a five-carbon sugar, and one or more phosphate groups. Nucleotides can carry chemical energy (e.g. ATP), form coenzymes (e.g. CoA), be used as specific signaling molecules (e.g. cAMP) in the cell. Nucleotides are the subunits of the nucleic acids.

Subject: fibril-associated collagen [IMR:0000544]
Value: associate with the surface of fibrils and modify their interactive properties.

Subject: eIF2 [IMR:0000902]
Value: heterotrimer of alpha, beta, gamma subunits. binds the initiator Met-tRNA to the 40S ribosomal subunit. GTP binding to eIF2 is necessary for formation of a stable eIF2:GTP:Met-tRNA ternary complex (TC). Following TC binding to the ribosome triggers GTP hydrolysis by eIF2.

Subject: eIF2B [IMR:0000903]
Value: heteropentamer of alpha, beta, gamma, delta, epsilon subunits. guanine nucleotide exchange factor (GEF) activity of eIF2B is necessary to recycle eIF2:GTP to eIF2:GTP.

Subject: eIF3 [IMR:0000904]
Value: consists of a core of five non-identical subunits (eIF3a, eIF3b, eIF3c, eIF3i and eIF3g in yeast) and up to six additional subunits in mammals (eIF3d, eIF3e, eIF3f, eIF3h, eIFj and eIF3k). binding to and stabilization of ternary complex, binding to the 40S ribosome, facilitating the binding of mRNA to the 40S ribosome, and promoting dissociation of 40S and 60S ribosomal subunits

Subject: eIF4A [IMR:0000906]
Value: eIF4A is a DEADbox helicase that can unwind RNA secondary structure in the cap-proximal region of the mRNA.

Subject: eIF4F [IMR:0000909]
Value: eIF4F is a heterotrimeric complex that binds to the cap structure at the 50 end of the mRNA. It is composed of eIF4G and the cap-binding protein eIF4E and the ATPdependent RNA helicase eIF4A.

Subject: 11S regulatory complex [IMR:0000919]
Value: composed of three related proteins, termed PA28alpha, PA28beta and PA28gamma. PA28alpha and PA28beta assemble into a heterohexameric complex with alternating a and b subunits, i.e. PA28(ab)3. In contrast, PA28gamma appears to form a homopolymeric complex, presumably PA28(g)6.

Subject: concentrative nucleoside transporter [IMR:0000927]
Value: concentrative nucleoside transporters cotranslocate nucleosides and sodium unidirectionally against the nucleoside concentration gradients and play a vital role in certain tissues.

Subject: equilibrative nucleoside transporter [IMR:0000928]
Value: translocate nucleosides and nucleobases bidirectionally down their concentration gradients and are important in the uptake of anticancer and antiviral nucleoside drugs.

Subject: DCO_DROME [IMR:0001391]
Value: dbt is 75% (719/947) identical at the nucleotide level and 86% (260/301) identical at the amino acid level to the kinase domain of human casein kinase I epsilon, suggesting that DBT is a structural homolog of this enzyme.

Subject: PNT2_DROME [IMR:0002979]
Value: pnt gene transcription generates alternatively spliced mRNA isoforms that encode two proteins, PntP1 and PntP2.    PntP2 is the homolog of the human Ets-1 transcription factor and functions as a transcriptional activator when phosphorylated by MAPK.

Subject: endothelin [IMR:0100166]
Value: 21-Amino-acid peptides produced by vascular endothelial cells and functioning as potent vasoconstrictors. The endothelin family consists of three members, ENDOTHELIN-1; ENDOTHELIN-2; and ENDOTHELIN-3. All three peptides contain 21 amino acids, but vary in amino acid composition. The three peptides produce vasoconstrictor and pressor responses in various parts of the body. However, the quantitative profiles of the pharmacological activities are considerably different among the three isopeptides.

Subject: cPKC [IMR:0100486]
Value: classical PKC isoforms (alpha, betaI, betaII and gamma) are regulated by calcium, diacylglycerol (DAG) and phospholipids.
